TowerScout YOLO-Enabled Release Notice

Release track: agpl-yolo

TowerScout is a browser-served Flask application for identifying cooling
towers from satellite and aerial imagery. The current YOLO-enabled release
package and container image include TowerScout-authored code, third-party
Python and JavaScript dependencies, Ultralytics YOLOv5 runtime source, and
separately supplied model/data assets.

Important release statement:

TowerScout-authored code may be Apache-2.0 where ownership and relicensing
authority are confirmed, but the full YOLO-enabled package/image is not an
Apache-2.0-only distribution. Because the release includes Ultralytics YOLOv5
AGPL-3.0 code and YOLO-derived detector weights, recipients must receive the
corresponding source and license notices required for the AGPL-governed
release track.

Corresponding source for each release must include:

- TowerScout source code for the exact release ref.
- Vendored Ultralytics YOLOv5 source under webapp/vendor/yolov5_local/.
- TowerScout local YOLO patches and loader code.
- Dockerfile, Compose files, launcher scripts, packaging scripts, and import
  helpers needed to rebuild and run the release.
- Python and frontend dependency manifests.
- Build, package, asset import, and run instructions.

The release control ZIP includes SOURCE.txt with the release source ref and
source-location instructions. The package also includes release-manifest.v1.json,
IMAGE.txt, SHA256SUMS.txt, SBOM.txt, MODEL_LICENSES.md, DATA_LICENSES.md,
PROVIDER_TERMS.md, and THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md.

The source and license notices are also exposed from the local web application
at /license when the app is running.
